<br>
If people leave the Firiona Vie server because they can't get a group... I'm OK with that.<br>
<br>
If people leave because they can't bind in dungeons, can't deal with langauage barriers, can't have more than one character, etc... I'm OK with that, too.<br>
<br>
I know, it's a harsh statement, but I love this server's low population. I have friends that I group with regularly, I've made more friends that know they can count on me when things get ugly.<br>
<br>
The low population &quot;forces&quot; this server to be more social, and that is a good thing. It forces you to actually talk with, and get to know, others so that you'll have people to call on when you want to hunt. In my opinion, that's all good.<br>
<br>
I actually feel sorry for anyone who thought things would be different here, specially if they have raced to the end-game in two months and are now bored. The Firiona Vie ruleset makes the endgame more challenging, which is a good thing in my opinion. But just because I feel sorry for them, doesn't mean I want to cater to them and have Verant start easing restrictions on this server.<br>
<br>
I think that if Verant starts &quot;easing&quot; any of the challenging/restrictive rules on this server, it will make the server worse, not better.<br>
<br>
If Verant feels they need to attract more people to the server, they should do it with incentives not compromises.<br>
<br>
