I kinda share your sentiment, Grim ... if you find the ruleset too difficult, maybe this is not the server for you.  The other servers don't have forced /roleplay.  If you've achieved 40+ in the last 2 or 3 months that FV has been up, I'm sure you can do it again (maybe faster) in another server.  But we'll miss the potential of your company.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, there are other things that may be bugs.  The different alignment groups and guilds, for one thing.  The TLC effects on some quest drops as another.<br>
<br>
So ... we should remain open to suggestions and discuss them further.  Maybe come up with solutions to present to the development team.<br>
<br>
The /lfg as a mandatory break of /anon and/or /roleplay has some potential.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll also introduce another idea to the original poster:  What if I don't want to be singled out in a /who?  Let's say I'm a cleric or enchanter who only trusts a certain small set of people to group up with.  I might be waiting in a zone for my friends and don't want to be bothered by all the other players.  If /roleplay was not forced, I would stand out -- after all, we all know to look for the /anon people in a /who to check for hiding druids and clerics. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 5:02:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small rules change needed for server health</span><hr size=1> I don't think the low population of FV is actually caused by the difficulties in finding a group directly.  Finding a group on FV maybe tricky and even difficult at some point, but it is still possible.  When I hunted in High pass, I got to know people around my level that is also hunting the areas.  I add to my friend list those who I find pleasent to group with.  My friend list is the source when I want to find someone to group with.  I believe grouping on FV is very different from the normal blue servers.  Instead of doing the amazing (and very unrealistic) who all cleric 40 60, one is actually forced to get to know a cleric and befriend with him/her.<br>
